CRE. If this was what he said, thou knowest for thyself; 

            for me, I claim to learn of thee in the same way 1 that thou 

            also hast now learnt of me.

Joc. I will send with all dispatch. But let us go within ; 

            naught will I do save what thou wishest done. (Exeunt 

            JOCASTA and ŒDIPUS into the palace.)  1 There is no reason to change πάθοςιnto άγος, as some have done.

ŒD. (still advancing). Do. thou, then, lead me, child, 

            where we may speak and hear, safe in piety's precincts ; 

            and let us not fight with necessity.

(ED. I will explain ; those whose blood I shed would e'en 

            have slain me;' wherefore, before the law, I am guiltless; 

            unwittingly I came to do this deed.

CRE. Indeed! and is it so? Well, be assured of this; 

            by Olympus yonder, thou shalt not revile me in addition to 

            thy reproaches without ruing it !

CHO. Daughter, in thy interests no less than mine I came ; 

            but, if I speak amiss, have thou thy way, for I will follow in 

            thy wake.

AGED A'IT. I will tell thee that, when the end cometh; 

            as things now are, 'tis well with all they do,—yea, e'en what 

            is not well.2

Thee, yes thee I ask, e'en 5 thee who wast erst so bold; 

            for it concerns thee most, I trow, and thou art like to know 

            and tell it best.

DEI. At least tell me, unhappy girl, with thy own lips; 

            yea, for I am indeed distressed, that I know not at least who 

            thou art.2

SECOND HALF-CHO. No doubtful sound is raised within; 

            nay, 'tis the wail of woe; the house hath some fresh 

            trouble.

The Chorus press for more details of their master's mad 

            doings; and Tecmessa again recounts all she has seen,-the 

            stealthy midnight sally ; the return with a mixed drove of cattle ; 

            the slaughter of the harmless beasts, and the wild abuse of 

            imaginary foes ; and, at last, the slow and painful recovery of 

            reason. " But," adds Tecmessa, " I fear there is worse to come ; 

            everything points to a fatal issue ; come and help me, if ye can ; 

            men of his stem mood will often listen to friends." (11. 281-332.)

ODY. Indeed I know none; yet I pity him in his wretched­ 

            ness, although he is my foe, seeing him fast bound to an 

            evil doom,-with an eye to mine own case as much as his; 

            for I see that all of us who live are nought but phantoms, 

            or an empty shadow.

CHO. And truly, Teucer, that was his commandment, 

            while as yet he lived, that thou should'st care for this child, 

            as indeed thou dost.

NEO. Well, but not so now at all; and I wish to hear 

            from thee, whether thy purpose is to stay here stubbornly, 

            or to sail with us.
